      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the capacitor looks fine after you've safely shut off the power, then yes, it's entirely possible that the issue lies elsewhere in the control system. Sometimes, a faulty relay, a bad contactor, or an intermittent wiring issue can prevent the electrical signal from properly engaging the motor, even if the capacitor is healthy. These electrical glitches are often harder to diagnose than a clearly broken component, which is why a trained technician is usually the best recourse.",
      "source": "target",
